FOR VEGETABLE BALLS-:
1/2 cup grated carrot
1/2 cup finely chopped cabbage(green)
1/4 cup finely chopped green bell pepper(capsicum)
1/4 cup finely chopped spring onions(scallions)
1/2 teaspoon freshly crushed black pepper or black pepper powder
2 tablespoons all purpose flour 
2 tablespoons cornfloor(corn starch)
1/2 teaspoon salt or add as per taste 
oil as required, for shallow or deep frying-sunflower oil or any neutral tasting oil

FOR GRAVY OR SAUCE-:
1 to 1.5 tablespoons oil-toasted sesame oil or sunflower oil or any neutral tasting oil
4 tablespoons finely chopped onions or chopped spring onion whites(scallion whites)
1 tablespoon finely chopped ginger 
1 tablespoon finely chopped garlic
2 green chillies-finely chopped 
1/4 cup finely chopped capsicum(green bell pepper)-optional
1 tablespoon finely chopped celery(optional)
1/2 tablespoon soy sauce
1 tablespoon tomato ketchup
2 to 3 teaspoon red chilli sauce(spicy not sweet)
1 teaspoon rice vinegar or regular white vinegar or apple cider vinegar
1 to 1.25 cups water or vegetable stock
1/2 teaspoon black pepper powder or freshly crushed black pepper 
salt to taste
1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon raw sugar to taste or white sugar-add as required
1 tablespoon spring onion green (scallion greens) for garnishing